HEADWORD: Spelding
<hw>Spel"ding</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Scot.
<ets>speld</ets> to spread out, <ets>spelder</ets> to split. spread
open; cf. G. <ets>spalten</ets> split.]</ety> <def>A haddock or other
small fish split open and dried in the sun; -- called also
<altname>speldron</altname>.</def> <mark>[Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spelicans</ent>⟦br⟧
